Detailed Description

When the Bluetooth Stack performs a service verify request the result of this request is stored in a memory block. The memory block allocated by the Bluetooth Stack will be copied in the constructor. From this time on it is independent from any other service verify request. So this class stores the size and a pointer to a memory block, for which the class is responsible to free at destruction.
There is no direct access to the memory block and it's size. Instead of this there are functions defined to get access to the single records. These functions do not copy any data. They only store a description of a record in the passed in BtSvrServiceRecord. So the application programmer has to provide the memory for the storage of the description.
The only point of execution, where memory is copied is in the constructor of BtServiceVerifyResult. All other access to the memory stored in BtServiceVerifyResult is done via references (pointers).
This is done so to ease the configuration of the memory pools and to avoid too many constructor calls for values that are not really needed by the application programmer.

BOOLEAN BtServiceVerifyResult::GetServiceRecordAtIndex (  UINT16  index,
BtSvrServiceRecord &  svr_service_record
)  const
 

Retrieve a service record from this service verify result.

GetSerivceRecordAtIndex returns the record at the position index of this service verify result. The index is zero based [0 .. numberOfRecords - 1].

Parameters:
index An UINT16 containing the index of the BtSvrServiceRecord that should be retrieved.
svr_service_record A reference to a BtSvrServiceRecord where to store the information of the retrieved record.
Returns:
TRUE: The index is valid and a description of the record is stored in svr_service_record.
FALSE: The index is out of bounds. Do not use the content of svr_service_record because it is not valid.

BOOLEAN BtServiceVerifyResult::IsValid (   )  const
 

Get validity of this service verify result.

IsValid returns the validity state of this service verify result.

Returns:
TRUE: This service verify result is valid. All other member functions return a result that can be used further.
FALSE: This service verify result is invalid. Do not call any further member functions because they allways will return an error.
